## HTML Overview

### What is HTML?

**HTML (HyperText Markup Language)** is the standard markup language for creating web pages. It provides the structure and content of web applications.

### Purpose of HTML

```
HTML → Structure & Content
CSS  → Styling & Layout
JS   → Behavior & Interactivity

HTML is the foundation - without it, CSS and JS have nothing to work with!
```

### Brief History

```
1989: Tim Berners-Lee invents HTML
1993: HTML 2.0 (first standardized version)
1997: HTML 4.0 (tables, stylesheets)
2000: XHTML (strict XML-based HTML)
2014: HTML5 (modern standard, still evolving)
2022+: HTML Living Standard (continuous evolution)
```

### Why Learn HTML Well?

1. **Foundation**: Everything on web is built with HTML
2. **SEO**: Proper HTML improves search engine ranking
3. **Accessibility**: Good HTML is accessible to everyone
4. **Performance**: Clean HTML loads faster
5. **Maintainability**: Well-written HTML is easier to maintain
6. **Professional**: Essential skill for all web developers

---

## HTML Concepts: Basic to Advanced

### Level 1: Absolute Beginner - What is HTML?

#### The Very Basics

HTML is a language that tells web browsers how to display content. Think of it like a blueprint for a house:

```
HTML = Structure (walls, rooms, layout)
CSS = Decoration (colors, furniture, design)
JS = Utilities (electricity, plumbing, functionality)
```

**Simple HTML Example:**

```html
<p>Hello, World!</p>
```

What happens:
1. Browser reads `<p>` tag
2. Browser knows: "This is a paragraph"
3. Browser displays the text
4. Browser closes with `</p>`

**KEY POINTS:**
- ✓ HTML is NOT a programming language (no logic/calculations)
- ✓ HTML just structures content
- ✓ Browser interprets HTML and displays it
- ✓ HTML is human-readable
- ✓ HTML files are plain text (can open in any editor)

---

### Level 2: Beginner - HTML Tags and Elements

#### Understanding Tags

**What is a tag?**

```html
<tagname>Content</tagname>
         ↑ Opening tag
                  ↑ Content
                        ↑ Closing tag
```

**Tag Types:**

```html
<!-- Container tags (have opening and closing) -->
<p>This is a paragraph</p>
<div>This is a division</div>

<!-- Self-closing tags (no closing tag needed) -->
<img src="image.jpg">
<br>
<hr>

<!-- Tags with attributes (properties) -->
<a href="https://example.com" title="Visit Example">Link</a>
        ↑ Attribute name   ↑ Attribute value
```

**Real Example:**

```html
<!-- Without structure -->
Home About Contact

<!-- With structure -->
<nav>
  <a href="/">Home</a>
  <a href="/about">About</a>
  <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
</nav>
```

Benefits: Browser understands it's navigation, screen readers understand it's a menu

**KEY POINTS:**
- ✓ Tags describe what content is (semantic meaning)
- ✓ Opening tag + Content + Closing tag = Element
- ✓ Attributes add extra information to tags
- ✓ Nesting: Tags inside tags must close in reverse order
- ✓ HTML is case-insensitive but lowercase is standard

#### Nesting Rules

```html
<!-- ✓ CORRECT: Proper nesting (close in reverse order) -->
<div>
  <p>Paragraph inside div</p>
</div>

<!-- ✗ WRONG: Overlapping tags -->
<div>
  <p>Paragraph
</div>
  </p>

<!-- ✓ CORRECT: Multiple nested levels -->
<section>
  <article>
    <p>Content</p>
  </article>
</section>
```

---

### Level 3: Beginner - Content and Text

#### Text Formatting

```html
<!-- Paragraphs (block-level, creates spacing) -->
<p>This is a paragraph.</p>
<p>This is another paragraph.</p>

<!-- Line break (single line) -->
<p>Line 1<br>Line 2</p>

<!-- Headings (hierarchy from h1 to h6) -->
<h1>Main Page Title (most important)</h1>
<h2>Section Title</h2>
<h3>Subsection Title</h3>

<!-- Text emphasis (semantic meaning) -->
<strong>Important text</strong>    <!-- Semantic: important -->
<b>Bold text</b>                   <!-- Visual: just bold -->

<em>Emphasized text</em>           <!-- Semantic: emphasize -->
<i>Italic text</i>                 <!-- Visual: just italic -->
```

**Example with Hierarchy:**

```html
<!-- ✓ CORRECT: Logical heading order -->
<h1>Product Store</h1>
<section>
  <h2>Featured Products</h2>
  <article>
    <h3>Product 1</h3>
    <p>Description</p>
  </article>
</section>

<!-- ✗ WRONG: Skipping levels -->
<h1>Product Store</h1>
<h3>Featured Products</h3>  <!-- Should be h2 -->
```

**Lists (organizing related items):**

```html
<!-- Unordered list (bullets) -->
<ul>
  <li>Item 1</li>
  <li>Item 2</li>
  <li>Item 3</li>
</ul>

<!-- Ordered list (numbers) -->
<ol>
  <li>First step</li>
  <li>Second step</li>
  <li>Third step</li>
</ol>

<!-- Nested lists -->
<ul>
  <li>Fruit
    <ul>
      <li>Apple</li>
      <li>Banana</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Vegetable</li>
</ul>
```

**KEY POINTS:**
- ✓ Heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3) matters for SEO and accessibility
- ✓ One h1 per page (main title)
- ✓ Use semantic tags (strong/em) instead of just visual (b/i)
- ✓ Lists make content scannable
- ✓ Proper structure helps screen readers

---

### Level 4: Intermediate - Forms and User Input

#### Form Basics

```html
<!-- Basic form -->
<form action="/submit" method="POST">
  <!-- Text input -->
  <label for="username">Username:</label>
  <input type="text" id="username" name="username" required>
  
  <!-- Submit button -->
  <button type="submit">Log In</button>
</form>
```

**Form Attributes Explained:**

```html
<form action="/endpoint"     <!-- Where to send data -->
      method="POST"          <!-- How to send (POST/GET) -->
      enctype="multipart/form-data">  <!-- For file uploads -->
  
  <!-- GET: Data in URL (max 2000 chars, visible, not secure) -->
  <!-- POST: Data in body (unlimited, hidden, more secure) -->
</form>
```

**Input Types (HTML5):**

```html
<!-- Text inputs -->
<input type="text" placeholder="Name">
<input type="email" placeholder="Email">
<input type="password" placeholder="Password">
<input type="number" min="0" max="100">
<input type="date">

<!-- Buttons -->
<input type="submit" value="Submit">
<input type="reset" value="Clear">
<input type="button" value="Click me">

<!-- Selection -->
<input type="checkbox"> (multiple selections)
<input type="radio">    (single selection)
<select>                (dropdown list)
<textarea>              (multi-line text)

<!-- HTML5 Validation -->
<input type="email" required>
<input type="text" minlength="3" maxlength="20">
<input type="number" min="0" max="100">
<input type="text" pattern="[0-9]{3}-[0-9]{3}">
```

**Complete Form Example:**

```html
<form method="POST" action="/register">
  <!-- Personal Information -->
  <fieldset>
    <legend>Personal Information</legend>
    
    <label for="name">Name *</label>
    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>
    
    <label for="email">Email *</label>
    <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
  </fieldset>
  
  <!-- Preferences -->
  <fieldset>
    <legend>Preferences</legend>
    
    <label for="interest">Interest:</label>
    <select id="interest" name="interest">
      <option value="">-- Select --</option>
      <option value="tech">Technology</option>
      <option value="sports">Sports</option>
    </select>
  </fieldset>
  
  <!-- Submit -->
  <button type="submit">Register</button>
</form>
```

**KEY POINTS:**
- ✓ Always use labels (for accessibility and usability)
- ✓ Use correct input types (not just type="text" for everything)
- ✓ Validate on HTML level first, then JavaScript, then server
- ✓ Method: POST for sensitive data, GET for searching
- ✓ Fieldset groups related inputs

---

### Level 5: Intermediate - HTML5 Features

#### Modern HTML Capabilities

**Audio and Video:**

```html
<!-- Audio player -->
<audio controls>
  <source src="song.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
  <source src="song.ogg" type="audio/ogg">
  Your browser doesn't support audio
</audio>

<!-- Video player -->
<video width="320" height="240" controls poster="thumbnail.jpg">
  <source src="movie.mp4" type="video/mp4">
  <source src="movie.webm" type="video/webm">
  Your browser doesn't support video
</video>

<!-- Video with captions -->
<video controls>
  <source src="movie.mp4" type="video/mp4">
  <track src="captions.vtt" kind="captions" srclang="en">
</video>
```

**Canvas (Drawing):**

```html
<canvas id="myCanvas" width="400" height="300"></canvas>

<script>
const canvas = document.getElementById('myCanvas');
const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');

// Draw shapes
ctx.fillStyle = 'red';
ctx.fillRect(10, 10, 100, 100);  // Rectangle

ctx.fillStyle = 'blue';
ctx.beginPath();
ctx.arc(200, 150, 50, 0, 2 * Math.PI);
ctx.fill();  // Circle

// Draw text
ctx.fillStyle = 'black';
ctx.font = '20px Arial';
ctx.fillText('Hello Canvas', 50, 250);
</script>
```

**Data Attributes (storing custom data):**

```html
<!-- Store data on elements -->
<div data-user-id="123" data-role="admin" data-status="active">
  User Profile
</div>

<script>
const div = document.querySelector('div');
console.log(div.dataset.userId);   // "123"
console.log(div.dataset.role);     // "admin"
console.log(div.dataset.status);   // "active"
</script>
```

**Geolocation API:**

```html
<button onclick="getLocation()">Get My Location</button>

<script>
function getLocation() {
  if (navigator.geolocation) {
    navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition(
      function(position) {
        console.log('Latitude: ' + position.coords.latitude);
        console.log('Longitude: ' + position.coords.longitude);
      },
      function(error) {
        console.error('Error: ' + error.message);
      }
    );
  }
}
</script>
```

**KEY POINTS:**
- ✓ HTML5 added native audio/video (no plugin needed)
- ✓ Canvas for drawing and graphics
- ✓ Data attributes store custom data
- ✓ Geolocation accesses user's location (with permission)
- ✓ LocalStorage persists data in browser

---

### Level 6: Advanced - Semantic and Accessibility

#### Semantic HTML Improves Everything

```html
<!-- ✗ BAD: All divs (meaningless to browser) -->
<div class="nav">
  <div class="item"><a href="/">Home</a></div>
  <div class="item"><a href="/about">About</a></div>
</div>
<div class="content">
  <div class="article">
    <div class="title">Article Title</div>
    <div class="body">Content here</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ✓ GOOD: Semantic elements (meaningful) -->
<nav>
  <a href="/">Home</a>
  <a href="/about">About</a>
</nav>
<main>
  <article>
    <h1>Article Title</h1>
    <p>Content here</p>
  </article>
</main>
```

**Benefits of Semantic HTML:**

```
1. SEO: Search engines understand structure
2. Accessibility: Screen readers know what things are
3. Maintainability: Code is self-documenting
4. Devices: Mobile devices optimize rendering
5. Future: Standards-based, will work forever
```

**ARIA (for complex interactions):**

```html
<!-- Describe interactive elements -->
<button aria-label="Close menu" onclick="closeMenu()">×</button>

<!-- Describe state -->
<div role="alert" aria-live="polite">
  Successfully saved!
</div>

<!-- Link descriptions -->
<button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="menu">Menu</button>
<div id="menu" hidden>Menu content</div>

<!-- Live updates (screen reader announces) -->
<div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
  You have 5 new messages
</div>
```

**Alt Text for Images:**

```html
<!-- ✓ GOOD: Descriptive alt text -->
<img src="chart.jpg" alt="Sales growth chart showing 25% increase Q1 to Q2">

<!-- ✗ BAD: Generic alt text -->
<img src="chart.jpg" alt="chart">

<!-- ✗ BAD: Redundant alt text -->
<img src="logo.png" alt="Company Logo">
<h1>Company Logo</h1>  <!-- Repeats the alt text -->

<!-- ✓ GOOD: Decorative images (empty alt) -->
<img src="decorative-line.png" alt="">

<!-- ✓ GOOD: Icon with meaning -->
<span aria-hidden="true">★</span> 5 stars
```

**KEY POINTS:**
- ✓ Use semantic elements first (header, nav, main, footer, article, section)
- ✓ ARIA for complex interactions (not overused)
- ✓ Alt text describes image, not just says "image"
- ✓ Keyboard navigation must work
- ✓ Color shouldn't be the only way to convey info

---

### Level 7: Advanced - Responsive and Modern

#### Responsive Images

```html
<!-- Basic responsive image -->
<img src="image-small.jpg"
     srcset="image-medium.jpg 768w,
             image-large.jpg 1200w"
     sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
            (max-width: 1200px) 80vw,
            60vw"
     alt="Responsive image">

<!-- Picture element (art direction) -->
<picture>
  <source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="image-mobile.jpg">
  <source media="(max-width: 1200px)" srcset="image-tablet.jpg">
  <img src="image-desktop.jpg" alt="Image">
</picture>

<!-- Modern image formats -->
<picture>
  <source srcset="image.webp" type="image/webp">
  <source srcset="image.png" type="image/png">
  <img src="image.png" alt="Image">
</picture>
```

**Meta Viewport (Essential for Mobile):**

```html
<!-- Without viewport: Page zoomed out on mobile -->
<!-- With viewport: Page fits mobile screen -->
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
```

**Preloading Resources:**

```html
<!-- Preload critical resources -->
<link rel="preload" href="font.woff2" as="font" type="font/woff2" crossorigin>
<link rel="preload" href="critical.css" as="style">

<!-- Prefetch future resources -->
<link rel="prefetch" href="next-page.html">

<!-- DNS prefetch for external services -->
<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//cdn.example.com">

<!-- Preconnect for important domains -->
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
```

**KEY POINTS:**
- ✓ Responsive images reduce data usage
- ✓ Picture element for art direction
- ✓ Modern formats (WebP) reduce file size
- ✓ Viewport meta tag is required for mobile
- ✓ Preload critical resources for performance

---

### Level 8: Advanced - Performance and SEO

#### Performance Optimization

```html
<!-- ✓ Scripts at bottom (defer loading) -->
<body>
  <!-- Content -->
  
  <script src="app.js" defer></script>  <!-- Load after DOM -->
  <script src="analytics.js" async></script>  <!-- Load in parallel -->
</body>

<!-- ✗ Scripts in head (blocks rendering) -->
<head>
  <script src="app.js"></script>  <!-- Blocks page display -->
</head>

<!-- Lazy loading images -->
<img src="image.jpg" alt="Description" loading="lazy">

<!-- Defer non-critical CSS -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
<link rel="preload" href="fonts.css" as="style" onload="this.onload=null;this.rel='stylesheet'">
```

#### SEO Best Practices

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <!-- Encoding (tells browser how to read text) -->
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  
  <!-- Viewport (mobile optimization) -->
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  
  <!-- Search result snippet -->
  <meta name="description" content="50-160 characters describing page">
  
  <!-- Unique, descriptive title -->
  <title>Main Keyword | Brand Name</title>
  
  <!-- Open Graph (social sharing) -->
  <meta property="og:title" content="Page Title">
  <meta property="og:description" content="Description">
  <meta property="og:image" content="image.jpg">
  <meta property="og:url" content="https://example.com">
  
  <!-- Canonical URL (for duplicate content) -->
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://example.com/page">
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Semantic structure aids SEO -->
  <h1>Main topic (use primary keyword)</h1>
  <h2>Subtopic</h2>
  <p>Content with related keywords</p>
  
  <!-- Structured data (Rich snippets in search) -->
  <article itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Article">
    <h1 itemprop="headline">Article Title</h1>
    <time itemprop="datePublished" datetime="2024-12-24">December 24, 2024</time>
    <span itemprop="author">John Doe</span>
    <p itemprop="articleBody">Content here</p>
  </article>
</body>
</html>
```

**Structured Data Example:**

```html
<!-- Rich snippet for recipes -->
<div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Recipe">
  <h1 itemprop="name">Chocolate Cake</h1>
  <img itemprop="image" src="cake.jpg" alt="Chocolate cake">
  <time itemprop="prepTime" datetime="PT20M">20 minutes</time>
  <span itemprop="recipeYield">8 servings</span>
  <p itemprop="description">Delicious cake recipe</p>
</div>
```

**KEY POINTS:**
- ✓ Meta description shows in search results
- ✓ Semantic structure helps search engines
- ✓ Structured data creates rich snippets
- ✓ Mobile-friendly is now a ranking factor
- ✓ Page speed affects ranking

---

### Level 9: Expert - Modern HTML Patterns

#### Progressive Enhancement

```html
<!-- Works without JavaScript -->
<form action="/search" method="GET">
  <input type="search" name="q" required>
  <button type="submit">Search</button>
</form>

<!-- Enhanced with JavaScript for better UX -->
<script>
document.querySelector('form').addEventListener('submit', function(e) {
  e.preventDefault();
  
  // Real-time search instead of page reload
  const query = this.querySelector('input[name="q"]').value;
  performLiveSearch(query);
});
</script>
```

**Web Components (reusable components):**

```html
<!-- Custom element -->
<my-button type="primary">Click me</my-button>
<my-card title="Product">Content here</my-card>

<script>
// Define custom element
class MyButton extends HTMLElement {
  connectedCallback() {
    this.innerHTML = `<button>${this.textContent}</button>`;
  }
}

customElements.define('my-button', MyButton);
</script>
```

**Shadow DOM (encapsulation):**

```html
<div id="host">Shadow DOM content</div>

<script>
const host = document.getElementById('host');
const shadowRoot = host.attachShadow({ mode: 'open' });

shadowRoot.innerHTML = `
  <style>
    p { color: red; }  /* Scoped styles */
  </style>
  <p>Isolated content</p>
`;
</script>
```

**Dynamic Content (templates):**

```html
<!-- Template (hidden until used) -->
<template id="item-template">
  <li class="item">
    <h3></h3>
    <p></p>
  </li>
</template>

<ul id="items"></ul>

<script>
const template = document.getElementById('item-template');
const items = [
  { title: 'Item 1', desc: 'Description 1' },
  { title: 'Item 2', desc: 'Description 2' }
];

items.forEach(item => {
  const clone = template.content.cloneNode(true);
  clone.querySelector('h3').textContent = item.title;
  clone.querySelector('p').textContent = item.desc;
  document.getElementById('items').appendChild(clone);
});
</script>
```

**KEY POINTS:**
- ✓ Progressive enhancement: Works without JavaScript
- ✓ Web Components for reusable, encapsulated elements
- ✓ Templates for dynamic content rendering
- ✓ Modern HTML works with frameworks (React, Vue, Angular)
- ✓ Semantic HTML is the foundation for everything

---

## HTML Fundamentals

### HTML Syntax: Tags and Attributes

```html
<!-- Opening and closing tags -->
<tagname>Content goes here</tagname>

<!-- Self-closing tags (no content) -->
<img src="image.jpg" alt="Description">
<br>
<hr>

<!-- Tags with attributes -->
<a href="https://example.com" title="Visit Example">Link</a>
<button class="btn" id="submit-btn" type="submit">Submit</button>

<!-- Nested tags (tag inside tag) -->
<div>
    <p>This paragraph is inside a div</p>
</div>
```

### Common HTML Attributes

```html
<!-- Global Attributes (available on all elements) -->
<element id="unique-id">                  <!-- Unique identifier -->
<element class="class-name">              <!-- CSS class -->
<element style="color: red;">             <!-- Inline styles -->
<element title="Tooltip text">            <!-- Hover tooltip -->
<element data-custom="value">             <!-- Custom data -->

<!-- Semantic Attributes -->
<element lang="en">                       <!-- Language -->
<element dir="rtl">                       <!-- Text direction -->
<element role="button">                   <!-- Accessibility role -->
<element aria-label="Label">              <!-- Screen reader label -->

<!-- Event Attributes -->
<element onclick="handleClick()">         <!-- Click event -->
<element onchange="handleChange()">       <!-- Change event -->
<element onsubmit="handleSubmit()">       <!-- Submit event -->
<element onload="handleLoad()">           <!-- Load event -->
```

### Document Structure

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>                           <!-- Document type declaration -->
<html lang="en">                          <!-- Root element -->
  <head>                                  <!-- Metadata container -->
    <meta charset="UTF-8">                <!-- Character encoding -->
    <meta name="viewport"                 <!-- Responsive design -->
          content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Page Title</title>              <!-- Browser tab title -->
  </head>
  <body>                                  <!-- Visible content -->
    <!-- Page content goes here -->
  </body>
</html>
```

### Common HTML Tags

```html
<!-- Text Formatting -->
<p>Paragraph</p>
<strong>Bold text (semantic)</strong>
<b>Bold text (styling)</b>
<em>Italic text (semantic)</em>
<i>Italic text (styling)</i>
<u>Underlined text</u>
<mark>Highlighted text</mark>
<small>Small text</small>
<del>Deleted text</del>
<ins>Inserted text</ins>

<!-- Headings -->
<h1>Most Important</h1>
<h2>Important</h2>
<h3>Less Important</h3>
<h4>Even Less</h4>
<h5>Minor</h5>
<h6>Least Important</h6>

<!-- Lists -->
<ul>                              <!-- Unordered list -->
  <li>Item 1</li>
  <li>Item 2</li>
</ul>

<ol>                              <!-- Ordered list -->
  <li>First</li>
  <li>Second</li>
</ol>

<dl>                              <!-- Description list -->
  <dt>Term</dt>
  <dd>Definition</dd>
</dl>

<!-- Links and Navigation -->
<a href="https://example.com">External link</a>
<a href="/about">Internal link</a>
<a href="#section">Anchor link</a>
<a href="mailto:email@example.com">Email link</a>
<a href="tel:+1234567890">Phone link</a>

<!-- Media -->
<img src="image.jpg" alt="Description">
<img src="image.jpg" alt="Description" width="300" height="200">
<picture>
  <source srcset="image-wide.jpg" media="(min-width: 768px)">
  <img src="image.jpg" alt="Description">
</picture>

<!-- Containers -->
<div>Generic container</div>
<section>Semantic section</section>
<article>Independent article</article>
<aside>Side content</aside>
<header>Header section</header>
<footer>Footer section</footer>
<main>Main content</main>
<nav>Navigation</nav>
```

---

## HTML Document Structure

### Proper Document Layout

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <!-- Meta information -->
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <meta name="description" content="Page description for SEO">
  <meta name="keywords" content="keyword1, keyword2">
  <meta name="author" content="Author Name">
  
  <!-- Title -->
  <title>Page Title | Website Name</title>
  
  <!-- Stylesheets -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
  
  <!-- Favicon -->
  <link rel="icon" href="favicon.ico">
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Header -->
  <header>
    <nav>
      <a href="/">Logo</a>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
        <li><a href="/contact">Contact</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </header>
  
  <!-- Main Content -->
  <main>
    <section id="hero">
      <h1>Welcome</h1>
      <p>Hero content</p>
    </section>
    
    <section id="content">
      <article>
        <h2>Article Title</h2>
        <p>Article content</p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
  
  <!-- Sidebar (if needed) -->
  <aside>
    <h3>Side Content</h3>
    <p>Secondary information</p>
  </aside>
  
  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer>
    <p>&copy; 2024 Website Name. All rights reserved.</p>
    <nav>
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
      <a href="/terms">Terms</a>
    </nav>
  </footer>
  
  <!-- Scripts -->
  <script src="app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Best Practices for Document Structure

```
✓ Use semantic HTML elements (not just divs)
✓ Proper nesting of elements
✓ One <h1> per page (for SEO and accessibility)
✓ Headings in hierarchical order (h1 → h2 → h3)
✓ Alt text for all images
✓ Descriptive page titles and meta descriptions
✓ Proper character encoding (UTF-8)
✓ Responsive viewport meta tag
✓ Logical content flow
✓ Skip links for navigation (accessibility)
```

---

## HTML Elements: Basic to Advanced

### Level 1: Text Elements

```html
<!-- Paragraphs and text -->
<p>This is a paragraph. It's a block-level element.</p>
<p>Multiple paragraphs can exist on the same page.</p>

<!-- Headings (hierarchy matters!) -->
<h1>Page Title</h1>
<h2>Section Title</h2>
<h3>Subsection Title</h3>

<!-- Line breaks and horizontal rules -->
<p>Line 1<br>Line 2</p>
<hr>

<!-- Preformatted text (preserves whitespace) -->
<pre>
  Code examples
    with indentation
      preserved exactly
</pre>

<!-- Blockquotes -->
<blockquote>
  <p>This is a quote from someone important.</p>
  <footer>— Person Name</footer>
</blockquote>

<!-- Addresses -->
<address>
  123 Main Street<br>
  City, State 12345
</address>
```

### Level 2: Lists and Organization

```html
<!-- Unordered list (bullets) -->
<ul>
  <li>Item 1</li>
  <li>Item 2</li>
  <li>Nested list:
    <ul>
      <li>Nested item 1</li>
      <li>Nested item 2</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<!-- Ordered list (numbers) -->
<ol>
  <li>First step</li>
  <li>Second step</li>
  <li>Third step</li>
</ol>

<!-- Description list (terms and definitions) -->
<dl>
  <dt>HTML</dt>
  <dd>HyperText Markup Language</dd>
  
  <dt>CSS</dt>
  <dd>Cascading Style Sheets</dd>
</dl>

<!-- Figure with caption -->
<figure>
  <img src="diagram.jpg" alt="Process diagram">
  <figcaption>Figure 1: The HTML Process</figcaption>
</figure>

<!-- Table -->
<table>
  <caption>Sales by Quarter</caption>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Quarter</th>
      <th>Sales</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Q1</td>
      <td>$1,000</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Q2</td>
      <td>$1,500</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
  <tfoot>
    <tr>
      <td>Total</td>
      <td>$2,500</td>
    </tr>
  </tfoot>
</table>
```

### Level 3: Forms and Input

```html
<!-- Basic form -->
<form action="/submit" method="POST">
  <!-- Text input -->
  <label for="name">Name:</label>
  <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>
  
  <!-- Email input -->
  <label for="email">Email:</label>
  <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
  
  <!-- Password input -->
  <label for="password">Password:</label>
  <input type="password" id="password" name="password" required>
  
  <!-- Select dropdown -->
  <label for="country">Country:</label>
  <select id="country" name="country">
    <option value="">-- Select Country --</option>
    <option value="us">United States</option>
    <option value="ca">Canada</option>
  </select>
  
  <!-- Textarea -->
  <label for="message">Message:</label>
  <textarea id="message" name="message" rows="5" cols="50"></textarea>
  
  <!-- Checkbox -->
  <input type="checkbox" id="agree" name="agree">
  <label for="agree">I agree to terms</label>
  
  <!-- Radio button -->
  <input type="radio" id="yes" name="answer" value="yes">
  <label for="yes">Yes</label>
  <input type="radio" id="no" name="answer" value="no">
  <label for="no">No</label>
  
  <!-- Submit button -->
  <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>
```

### Level 4: Advanced HTML5 Elements

```html
<!-- Data list (auto-complete) -->
<label for="browser">Choose browser:</label>
<input list="browsers" id="browser" name="browser">
<datalist id="browsers">
  <option value="Chrome">
  <option value="Firefox">
  <option value="Safari">
</datalist>

<!-- Progress bar -->
<progress id="progress" max="100" value="70"></progress>

<!-- Meter (for measurements) -->
<meter id="storage" max="100" value="65"></meter>

<!-- Time/Date -->
<label for="event">Date and time:</label>
<input type="datetime-local" id="event" name="event">

<!-- Search input -->
<label for="search">Search:</label>
<input type="search" id="search" name="search" placeholder="Search...">

<!-- Color picker -->
<label for="color">Pick a color:</label>
<input type="color" id="color" name="color" value="#FF0000">

<!-- Range slider -->
<label for="volume">Volume:</label>
<input type="range" id="volume" name="volume" min="0" max="100" value="50">

<!-- Output element (for calculation results) -->
<form oninput="result.value = parseInt(a.value) + parseInt(b.value)">
  <input type="number" id="a" value="10">
  +
  <input type="number" id="b" value="20">
  =
  <output id="result" name="result"></output>
</form>

<!-- Canvas (for drawing) -->
<canvas id="myCanvas" width="300" height="200"></canvas>

<!-- SVG (Scalable Vector Graphics) -->
<svg width="100" height="100">
  <circle cx="50" cy="50" r="40" fill="red"></circle>
</svg>

<!-- Iframe (embed another page) -->
<iframe src="https://example.com" width="600" height="400"></iframe>

<!-- Embed media -->
<embed src="video.mp4" type="video/mp4" width="400" height="300">

<!-- Object element -->
<object data="document.pdf" type="application/pdf" width="600" height="800"></object>

<!-- Template (hidden until used by JavaScript) -->
<template id="article-template">
  <article>
    <h3></h3>
    <p></p>
  </article>
</template>
```

---

## Semantic HTML

### What is Semantic HTML?

Semantic HTML uses elements that clearly describe their meaning and purpose to both browsers and developers.

```html
<!-- ✗ Non-semantic (only divs) -->
<div class="header">
  <div class="nav">
    <div class="nav-item"><a href="/">Home</a></div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="content">
  <div class="article">
    <div class="title">Article Title</div>
    <div class="body">Content here</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ✓ Semantic (meaningful elements) -->
<header>
  <nav>
    <a href="/">Home</a>
  </nav>
</header>
<main>
  <article>
    <h1>Article Title</h1>
    <p>Content here</p>
  </article>
</main>
```

### Semantic Elements

```html
<!-- Page Structure -->
<header>      Top of page (logo, nav, title)</header>
<nav>         Navigation links</nav>
<main>        Primary content of page</main>
<section>     Thematic grouping of content</section>
<article>     Independent, self-contained content</article>
<aside>       Sidebar or supplementary content</aside>
<footer>      Bottom of page (copyright, links)</footer>

<!-- Text Semantics -->
<strong>     Important text (semantic bold)</strong>
<em>         Emphasized text (semantic italic)</em>
<mark>       Highlighted/marked text</mark>
<code>       Code snippet</code>
<kbd>        Keyboard input</kbd>
<var>        Variable or placeholder</var>
<samp>       Sample output</samp>

<!-- Grouping -->
<figure>      Illustration, diagram, image with caption</figure>
<figcaption>  Caption for figure</figcaption>
<details>     Collapsible content</details>
<summary>     Summary/heading for details</summary>
<time>        Date/time</time>
<address>     Contact information</address>
```

### Semantic Examples

```html
<!-- Blog Structure -->
<article>
  <header>
    <h1>Article Title</h1>
    <time datetime="2024-12-24">December 24, 2024</time>
  </header>
  <p>Article content</p>
  <footer>
    <p>By <strong>Author Name</strong></p>
  </footer>
</article>

<!-- Site Structure -->
<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Site Title</h1>
    <nav>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </header>
  
  <main>
    <section id="featured">
      <h2>Featured Content</h2>
      <!-- Content -->
    </section>
    
    <section id="latest">
      <h2>Latest Posts</h2>
      <article>
        <h3>Post 1</h3>
        <!-- Content -->
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
  
  <aside>
    <h3>Related Links</h3>
    <!-- Content -->
  </aside>
  
  <footer>
    <p>&copy; 2024</p>
  </footer>
</body>

<!-- Collapsible Section -->
<details>
  <summary>More Information</summary>
  <p>This text is hidden by default and can be toggled.</p>
</details>
```

### Benefits of Semantic HTML

```
✓ Better SEO (search engines understand structure)
✓ Accessibility (screen readers understand meaning)
✓ Maintainability (code is self-documenting)
✓ Consistency (team understands structure)
✓ Future-proof (standards are built on semantics)
✓ Mobile-friendly (semantic elements are responsive)
```

---

## Forms and Input Types

### Form Structure

```html
<form action="/submit-form" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
  <!-- Form fields here -->
  
  <button type="submit">Submit</button>
  <button type="reset">Reset</button>
</form>
```

**Form Attributes:**
- `action`: Where to submit form
- `method`: GET (URL) or POST (secure)
- `enctype`: Encoding type (multipart for files)
- `name`: Form identifier
- `target`: Where to open response

### Input Types (HTML5)

```html
<!-- Text inputs -->
<input type="text" placeholder="Text">
<input type="email" placeholder="email@example.com">
<input type="password" placeholder="Password">
<input type="url" placeholder="https://example.com">
<input type="tel" placeholder="+1 (555) 000-0000">
<input type="search" placeholder="Search query">

<!-- Number and range -->
<input type="number" min="0" max="100" step="5">
<input type="range" min="0" max="100">

<!-- Date and time -->
<input type="date">
<input type="time">
<input type="datetime-local">
<input type="month">
<input type="week">

<!-- File upload -->
<input type="file" accept="image/*">
<input type="file" accept=".pdf,.doc" multiple>

<!-- Color picker -->
<input type="color" value="#FF0000">

<!-- Hidden field -->
<input type="hidden" name="csrf-token" value="token-here">

<!-- Buttons -->
<button type="submit">Submit</button>
<button type="reset">Reset</button>
<button type="button">Custom Button</button>
```

### Form Validation

```html
<!-- HTML5 Validation (built-in) -->
<form>
  <!-- Required field -->
  <input type="text" required>
  
  <!-- Email validation -->
  <input type="email" required>
  
  <!-- Pattern validation (regex) -->
  <input type="text" pattern="[0-9]{3}-[0-9]{3}-[0-9]{4}"
         placeholder="XXX-XXX-XXXX" title="Phone number format">
  
  <!-- Length validation -->
  <input type="text" minlength="3" maxlength="20">
  
  <!-- Number range -->
  <input type="number" min="0" max="100">
  
  <!-- Custom validation message -->
  <input type="email" required
         oninvalid="this.setCustomValidity('Please enter valid email')">
</form>

<!-- Custom validation with JavaScript -->
<form id="myForm">
  <input type="password" id="password" required>
  <input type="password" id="confirm" required>
  <button type="submit">Register</button>
</form>

<script>
const form = document.getElementById('myForm');
form.addEventListener('submit', function(e) {
  e.preventDefault();
  
  const password = document.getElementById('password').value;
  const confirm = document.getElementById('confirm').value;
  
  if (password !== confirm) {
    alert('Passwords do not match!');
    return false;
  }
  
  form.submit();
});
</script>
```

### Accessible Forms

```html
<form>
  <!-- Proper labels -->
  <label for="username">Username:</label>
  <input type="text" id="username" name="username" required>
  
  <!-- Grouped related inputs -->
  <fieldset>
    <legend>Select your options:</legend>
    
    <input type="checkbox" id="opt1" name="options" value="1">
    <label for="opt1">Option 1</label>
    
    <input type="checkbox" id="opt2" name="options" value="2">
    <label for="opt2">Option 2</label>
  </fieldset>
  
  <!-- Help text -->
  <label for="password">Password:</label>
  <input type="password" id="password" name="password" 
         aria-describedby="pwd-hint" required>
  <small id="pwd-hint">At least 8 characters</small>
  
  <!-- Error messages -->
  <label for="email">Email:</label>
  <input type="email" id="email" name="email" 
         aria-describedby="email-error" required>
  <span id="email-error" role="alert">Please enter valid email</span>
</form>
```

---

## Accessibility

### Why Accessibility Matters

```
✓ Legal requirement (WCAG, ADA)
✓ Ethical responsibility
✓ Improves SEO
✓ Better for all users (captions help in noisy environments)
✓ Larger audience reach
✓ Better code quality overall
```

### Semantic HTML for Accessibility

```html
<!-- ✓ Good: Semantic elements -->
<button>Click me</button>
<nav>Navigation</nav>
<header>Page header</header>

<!-- ✗ Bad: Non-semantic elements -->
<div onclick="handleClick()">Click me</div>
<div class="nav">Navigation</div>
<div class="header">Page header</div>
```

### ARIA (Accessible Rich Internet Applications)

```html
<!-- Role attribute -->
<div role="button" tabindex="0">Custom button</div>
<div role="alert">Important message</div>
<div role="progressbar" aria-valuenow="70" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100"></div>

<!-- Label and description -->
<button aria-label="Close menu">×</button>
<div aria-describedby="hint">Field</div>
<small id="hint">Help text</small>

<!-- Live regions (announce updates) -->
<div aria-live="polite">
  Page updated with 5 new messages
</div>

<!-- Hidden from accessibility tree -->
<span aria-hidden="true">★★★★★</span>

<!-- Expanded/Collapsed state -->
<button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="menu">Menu</button>
<div id="menu" hidden>Menu content</div>
```

### Alt Text for Images

```html
<!-- ✓ Good: Descriptive alt text -->
<img src="graph.jpg" alt="Sales growth chart showing 25% increase over last quarter">

<!-- ✗ Bad: Empty alt text (for decorative images) -->
<img src="spacer.gif" alt="">

<!-- ✗ Bad: Generic alt text -->
<img src="photo.jpg" alt="photo">

<!-- ✗ Bad: Redundant alt text (with nearby text) -->
<img src="logo.png" alt="Company Logo">
<h1>Company Logo</h1>

<!-- Icons with text -->
<span aria-hidden="true">★</span> 5 stars

<!-- Images that are links -->
<a href="/home" aria-label="Home page">
  <img src="home-icon.png" alt="">
</a>
```

### Keyboard Navigation

```html
<!-- Tabindex for custom elements -->
<div tabindex="0">Focusable with Tab key</div>
<div tabindex="1">Higher priority</div>
<div tabindex="-1">Cannot tab to (but focusable via JS)</div>

<!-- Skip links -->
<body>
  <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>
  
  <header>Navigation</header>
  <main id="main-content">Main content</main>
</body>

<!-- Keyboard traps (should be avoided!) -->
<!-- ✗ Don't do this -->
<div onkeydown="if(event.keyCode===27) return false;">
  Trap user in modal
</div>
```

### Color and Contrast

```html
<!-- Sufficient contrast ratio (4.5:1 minimum) -->
<p style="color: #333; background-color: #fff;">Good contrast</p>

<!-- Don't rely on color alone -->
<p>Required field: <span style="color: red;">*</span></p>
<p>Required field: <span style="color: red;" aria-label="required">*</span></p>

<!-- Color blindness considerations -->
<div style="color: red;">Error message</div>
<div style="color: red;"> ❌ Error: Something went wrong</div>
```

### Testing Accessibility

```html
<!-- WAVE browser extension -->
<!-- Lighthouse (Chrome DevTools) -->
<!-- Screen reader (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver) -->
<!-- Keyboard only navigation -->
<!-- Automated testing: axe-core, jest-axe -->

<!-- Example with aria attributes -->
<form aria-labelledby="form-title">
  <h2 id="form-title">Contact Us</h2>
  
  <label for="name">Name (required):</label>
  <input id="name" type="text" required aria-required="true">
  
  <label for="email">Email (required):</label>
  <input id="email" type="email" required aria-required="true">
  
  <button type="submit" aria-busy="false" id="submit">Send</button>
</form>
```

---

## HTML5 Features

### Audio and Video

```html
<!-- Audio element -->
<audio controls>
  <source src="audio.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
  <source src="audio.ogg" type="audio/ogg">
  Your browser doesn't support audio element
</audio>

<!-- Video element -->
<video width="320" height="240" controls poster="image.jpg">
  <source src="video.mp4" type="video/mp4">
  <source src="video.webm" type="video/webm">
  Your browser doesn't support video element
</video>

<!-- Tracks for captions/subtitles -->
<video controls>
  <source src="video.mp4" type="video/mp4">
  <track src="subtitles-en.vtt" kind="subtitles" srclang="en" label="English">
  <track src="captions-en.vtt" kind="captions" srclang="en" label="English">
</video>

<!-- Audio with controls -->
<audio controls preload="metadata">
  <source src="podcast.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">
</audio>
```

### Canvas (Drawing)

```html
<canvas id="myCanvas" width="400" height="300"></canvas>

<script>
const canvas = document.getElementById('myCanvas');
const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');

// Draw rectangle
ctx.fillStyle = 'red';
ctx.fillRect(10, 10, 150, 100);

// Draw circle
ctx.fillStyle = 'blue';
ctx.beginPath();
ctx.arc(200, 150, 50, 0, 2 * Math.PI);
ctx.fill();

// Draw text
ctx.fillStyle = 'black';
ctx.font = '20px Arial';
ctx.fillText('Hello Canvas', 50, 250);

// Draw line
ctx.strokeStyle = 'green';
ctx.lineWidth = 3;
ctx.beginPath();
ctx.moveTo(10, 50);
ctx.lineTo(300, 50);
ctx.stroke();
</script>
```

### SVG (Scalable Vector Graphics)

```html
<!-- SVG Container -->
<svg width="200" height="200" viewBox="0 0 200 200">
  <!-- Rectangle -->
  <rect x="10" y="10" width="100" height="100" fill="red" stroke="black" stroke-width="2"/>
  
  <!-- Circle -->
  <circle cx="150" cy="50" r="40" fill="blue"/>
  
  <!-- Line -->
  <line x1="10" y1="150" x2="190" y2="150" stroke="green" stroke-width="2"/>
  
  <!-- Polygon -->
  <polygon points="100,10 40,198 190,78" fill="yellow" stroke="black" stroke-width="2"/>
  
  <!-- Text -->
  <text x="50" y="180" font-size="20" fill="black">SVG Text</text>
  
  <!-- Path (complex shapes) -->
  <path d="M 10 80 Q 95 10 180 80" stroke="purple" stroke-width="2" fill="none"/>
</svg>
```

### Web Storage

```html
<!-- localStorage (persistent) -->
<script>
// Save data
localStorage.setItem('username', 'john');
localStorage.setItem('preferences', JSON.stringify({theme: 'dark'}));

// Retrieve data
const username = localStorage.getItem('username');
const prefs = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('preferences'));

// Remove data
localStorage.removeItem('username');

// Clear all
localStorage.clear();
</script>

<!-- sessionStorage (session only) -->
<script>
sessionStorage.setItem('session-id', 'abc123');
const sessionId = sessionStorage.getItem('session-id');
sessionStorage.removeItem('session-id');
sessionStorage.clear();
</script>
```

### Geolocation API

```html
<button onclick="getLocation()">Get My Location</button>
<p id="result"></p>

<script>
function getLocation() {
  if (navigator.geolocation) {
    navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition(showPosition, showError);
  } else {
    document.getElementById('result').innerText = 'Geolocation not supported';
  }
}

function showPosition(position) {
  const lat = position.coords.latitude;
  const lng = position.coords.longitude;
  document.getElementById('result').innerText = `Latitude: ${lat}, Longitude: ${lng}`;
}

function showError(error) {
  console.error('Error getting location:', error.message);
}
</script>
```

