## Media

### Images

```html
<!-- Basic image -->
<img src="image.jpg" alt="Description">

<!-- Responsive images (srcset) -->
<img src="image-default.jpg"
     srcset="image-small.jpg 480w,
             image-medium.jpg 768w,
             image-large.jpg 1200w"
     sizes="(max-width: 480px) 100vw,
            (max-width: 768px) 80vw,
            60vw"
     alt="Description">

<!-- Picture element (art direction) -->
<picture>
  <source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="image-mobile.jpg">
  <source media="(max-width: 1200px)" srcset="image-tablet.jpg">
  <img src="image-desktop.jpg" alt="Description">
</picture>

<!-- Image with figure and caption -->
<figure>
  <img src="sunset.jpg" alt="Beautiful sunset">
  <figcaption>Sunset at the beach</figcaption>
</figure>

<!-- Image maps (clickable regions) -->
<img src="map.jpg" alt="Map" usemap="#mymap">
<map name="mymap">
  <area shape="rect" coords="0,0,100,100" href="/location1" alt="Location 1">
  <area shape="circle" coords="150,150,50" href="/location2" alt="Location 2">
</map>
```

### Embedded Media

```html
<!-- Embedded iframe -->
<iframe src="https://example.com" 
        width="600" height="400"
        title="Example Website"></iframe>

<!-- Embedded video player (YouTube) -->
<iframe width="560" height="315" 
        src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/dQw4w9WgXcQ"
        title="YouTube video player"
        frameborder="0" 
        allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
        allowfullscreen></iframe>

<!-- Embed external content -->
<embed src="document.pdf" type="application/pdf" width="600" height="800">

<!-- Object element -->
<object data="animation.swf" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" 
        width="600" height="400"></object>
```

---

## Performance and Best Practices

### HTML Best Practices

```html
<!-- ✓ Good -->
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
<script src="app.js" defer></script>

<!-- ✗ Avoid -->
<style>body { color: red; }</style>  <!-- Inline styles in HTML -->
<script>console.log('Inline JS')</script>  <!-- Inline scripts in HTML -->
<script src="app.js"></script>  <!-- Without defer/async -->

<!-- Semantic structure -->
<body>
  <header></header>
  <nav></nav>
  <main>
    <section></section>
  </main>
  <aside></aside>
  <footer></footer>
</body>

<!-- Proper heading hierarchy -->
<h1>Page Title</h1>
<h2>Section</h2>
<h3>Subsection</h3>
<!-- Don't skip levels: h1 → h3 is bad -->

<!-- Alt text for images -->
<img src="chart.png" alt="Sales chart showing 30% growth">

<!-- Descriptive link text -->
<a href="/about">Learn more about us</a>
<!-- Not: <a href="/about">Click here</a> -->

<!-- Form labels -->
<label for="email">Email:</label>
<input id="email" type="email" name="email">
<!-- Not: <input type="email"> without label -->
```

### Performance Tips

```html
<!-- 1. Defer script loading -->
<script src="app.js" defer></script>  <!-- Load after DOM is parsed -->
<script src="analytics.js" async></script>  <!-- Load in parallel, non-blocking -->

<!-- 2. Lazy load images -->
<img src="image.jpg" alt="Description" loading="lazy">

<!-- 3. Use modern image formats -->
<picture>
  <source srcset="image.webp" type="image/webp">
  <source srcset="image.jpg" type="image/jpeg">
  <img src="image.jpg" alt="Description">
</picture>

<!-- 4. Responsive images to avoid unnecessary downloads -->
<img srcset="small.jpg 480w, medium.jpg 768w, large.jpg 1200w"
     src="medium.jpg" alt="Description">

<!-- 5. Preload critical resources -->
<link rel="preload" href="font.woff2" as="font" type="font/woff2" crossorigin>
<link rel="preload" href="critical.css" as="style">

<!-- 6. DNS prefetch for external resources -->
<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//cdn.example.com">

<!-- 7. Resource hints -->
<link rel="prefetch" href="future-page.html">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
```

### SEO Best Practices

```html
<!-- Proper meta tags -->
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="description" content="Page description (max 160 chars)">
<meta name="keywords" content="keyword1, keyword2">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

<!-- Proper title -->
<title>Unique, Descriptive Title | Brand Name</title>

<!-- Semantic structure -->
<h1>Main Page Title</h1>
<h2>Section Heading</h2>
<p>Paragraph with keywords</p>

<!-- Structured data (Schema.org) -->
<article itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Article">
  <h1 itemprop="headline">Article Title</h1>
  <time itemprop="datePublished" datetime="2024-12-24">December 24, 2024</time>
  <span itemprop="author">John Doe</span>
  <p itemprop="articleBody">Content here</p>
</article>

<!-- Open Graph for social sharing -->
<meta property="og:title" content="Page Title">
<meta property="og:description" content="Page description">
<meta property="og:image" content="image.jpg">
<meta property="og:url" content="https://example.com">

<!-- Twitter Card -->
<meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image">
<meta name="twitter:title" content="Page Title">
<meta name="twitter:image" content="image.jpg">
```

---

## Real-World Scenarios

### Scenario 1: Product Page

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Premium Headphones | Audio Store</title>
  <meta name="description" content="High-quality wireless headphones with noise cancellation">
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <nav>
      <a href="/">Store</a>
      <a href="/cart">Cart</a>
    </nav>
  </header>
  
  <main>
    <section class="product">
      <h1>Premium Wireless Headphones</h1>
      
      <picture>
        <source srcset="product-mobile.jpg" media="(max-width: 600px)">
        <source srcset="product-tablet.jpg" media="(max-width: 1200px)">
        <img src="product-desktop.jpg" alt="Premium wireless headphones in black">
      </picture>
      
      <div class="details">
        <p><strong>Price:</strong> $199.99</p>
        <p><strong>Features:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Active noise cancellation</li>
          <li>40-hour battery life</li>
          <li>Premium sound quality</li>
        </ul>
        
        <form method="POST" action="/add-to-cart">
          <label for="quantity">Quantity:</label>
          <input type="number" id="quantity" name="quantity" min="1" value="1" required>
          
          <button type="submit">Add to Cart</button>
        </form>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <section class="reviews">
      <h2>Customer Reviews</h2>
      <article>
        <h3>Great Product</h3>
        <p><strong>Rating:</strong> ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐</p>
        <p>Excellent sound quality and comfortable to wear.</p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
  
  <footer>
    <p>&copy; 2024 Audio Store. All rights reserved.</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

### Scenario 2: Contact Form

```html
<form action="/submit-contact" method="POST">
  <fieldset>
    <legend>Contact Information</legend>
    
    <div class="form-group">
      <label for="name">Name *</label>
      <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required
             minlength="2" maxlength="100">
    </div>
    
    <div class="form-group">
      <label for="email">Email *</label>
      <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
    </div>
    
    <div class="form-group">
      <label for="phone">Phone</label>
      <input type="tel" id="phone" name="phone"
             pattern="[0-9\-\+\(\)\s]*">
    </div>
  </fieldset>
  
  <fieldset>
    <legend>Your Message</legend>
    
    <div class="form-group">
      <label for="subject">Subject *</label>
      <input type="text" id="subject" name="subject" required>
    </div>
    
    <div class="form-group">
      <label for="category">Category *</label>
      <select id="category" name="category" required>
        <option value="">-- Select Category --</option>
        <option value="support">Support</option>
        <option value="sales">Sales</option>
        <option value="feedback">Feedback</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    
    <div class="form-group">
      <label for="message">Message *</label>
      <textarea id="message" name="message" required
                rows="5" minlength="10" maxlength="1000"></textarea>
    </div>
    
    <div class="form-group">
      <input type="checkbox" id="newsletter" name="newsletter">
      <label for="newsletter">Subscribe to our newsletter</label>
    </div>
  </fieldset>
  
  <div class="form-actions">
    <button type="submit">Send Message</button>
    <button type="reset">Clear Form</button>
  </div>
</form>
```

